&lt;p&gt;North Bristol NHS Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinical Fellow in Neonatal Medicine (ST4+ Level)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(Full time)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a Clinical Fellow post in Neonatal Medicine (ST 4+ level) to gain tertiary medical neonatal experience based at Southmead Hospital in Neonates&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The posts will start 4th January 2021 (or soon after) until 31st August 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Southmead (16 Intensive/high dependency cots) is a tertiary medical Neonatal Unit and joint lead centre for the Western Neonatal Network (WNN). Approximately 5,500 babies are born each year at Southmead Hospital. The Neonatal Unit provides a full range of Medical Intensive Care accepting tertiary medical referrals from WNN as well as providing a tertiary service in Neonatal Neurology for the South West of England. There is a strong emphasis on teaching, research and evidence-based medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The postholder will be required to work a full shift system whilst at this hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full Registration with the GMC is essential. Experience and familiarity with UK hospital systems and practices or equivalent is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The posts are not recognised for training and do not have postgraduate deanery approval; however, the job is educationally sound.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The annual salary is £31,841 - £50,068. This post also attracts a supplement of 50% of the basic salary for working on the out of hours rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are shortlisted we will contact you by email with details of your interview of which you will need to confirm your attendance. Therefore it is important that you check your online account regularly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note North Bristol NHS Trust will not pay interview expenses in connection with this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Late applications will not be accepted&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Committed to equal opportunities, job share applications welcome&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr R Wach’s secretaryAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The current junior doctors in post via the hospital switchboard or Dr R Wach’s secretary at Southmead Hospital on 0117 9505050 ext 5325&lt;/p&gt;
